<TITLE> WB to help Comilla EPZ expansion </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, July 17 (bdnews24.com) - The World Bank will provide financial assistance for expansion of the Comilla Export Processing Zone, BEPZA said in a statement Tuesday. The multilateral lender expressed interest to do so when a six-member team led by Erik D Mannes, senior private sector development specialist of the bank, met Brig. General Ashraf Abdullah Yussuf, executive chairman of the Bangladesh Export Processing Zones Authority, the statement said. The WB team proposed formation of a private-public partnership to expand the EPZs. It also talked about expanding the Comilla EPZ as part of a Special Economic Zone. The Comilla EPZ faces high demand for plots as it has already allotted most of the 208 industrial plots for establishment of 39 enterprises. Out of the 39 enterprises, 16 industrial units, employing over 5,000 local and foreign nationals, are in operation. "We see high demand for plots in the Comilla EPZ. Majority of the plots have been allotted," the official said. The EPZ was set up in 2004 in an area of about 270 acres of land. At present, 285 industries are in operation in the country's eight EPZs and employ over 2 lakh Bangladeshis bdn
